  <summary>9/5/1997--Introduced.
Repeals the Military Selective Service Act. States that, notwithstanding provisions of such Act, the Office of Selective Service Records shall not be reestablished upon such repeal. Transfers assets, contracts, property, and records held by the Selective Service System, as well as unexpended appropriations, to the Administrator of General Services.</summary>
